              "question": "What does entropy measure?",
              "answer": "Entropy is a measure of the disorder in the system."
            },
            {
              "question": "What happens to entropy when disorder in the system increases?",
              "answer": "Entropy increases, so ΔS is positive."
            },
            {
              "question": "Why does entropy generally increase when particles move more freely?",
              "answer": "There are more possible ways to arrange the particles and energy in the system."
